metadata.name: Unicorn #7784
metadata.description:
All of us have dreams, and everyone would like to meet a fairy, a genie, a wizard, or someone else who will make our dreams come true in a snap of a finger or with the wave of a wand. But we're the only ones who can do it. We are those magical unicorns, unique, inimitable, with our own qualities and magical abilities.
These unicorns are the visualization of our inner selves that makes our dreams come true. An embodiment of all the best with a huge positive magical power.

metadata.name: Antigravity #259
metadata.description:
To change size or quality, open the IPFS link in a separate window and append to its url a string like `&quality=400&tiles=9,16`. You may notice two parameters in it: `quality` and `tiles`.

`quality` is an integer from 1 to ~1000, the better the quality — the slower the rendering. Default is 200.

`tiles` is a number of 256×256 px tiles to render. Can be an integer (for square images) or two integers separated with a comma (for rectangular). `tiles=9,16` will make an image with width of 9×256 px = 2304 px and height of 16×256 px = 4096 px. If not set, adapts to screen size.

Press `s` to save the image.

metadata.name: Drifters #219
metadata.description:
In an undiscovered area, you've stumbled upon an unknown creature.
It looks weirdly haunting, and you're feeling a sense of unease.

You're wondering what it's doing.

It seems to move in patterns, and sometimes suddenly changes course.
Is it communicating?

(to whom?)

Setting aside your discomfort for a moment, you're realizing you could be seeing it wrong.
While the creature does look eerie and its motivations are unclear,
you realize every culture has its own appreciation of aesthetics,
and you can't help noticing there is a certain grace to this performance.

And it all makes sense.

You're witnessing uncharted explorations of elegance.

–

Append [?scale=<number>] to the url to scale the renderer.
Press [control / command + s] to save the current frame to a file.

© 2022 Monokai.

metadata.name: A Map Of Life #3
metadata.description:
On Wednesday May 4th 2022 at Arroz Estudios (Lisbon), Karen & Dora presented a workshop around their residence theme, "Sou daqui/Não sou daqui" ("I'm from here/I'm not from here").
 
With a dozen artists we have been exploring the sense of feeling like a foreigner in our own country through movement, dance and physical theater.
We especially had discussions over the places that gave us the “least feeling of belonging”, or “the best feeling of belonging”... and we ended up with the very ambitious project of drawing a map of our life in 15 minutes!
This generative token was created as a continuation of the workshop, and is also inspired by the talks with my workshop partner Laura. The "LIVE" mode is a tribute to Karen and Dora as performing artists. 
 
20% of the royalties amount will be transferred to Arroz Estudios’ wallet, and 10% to the minter.
 
The canvas size gets adjusted to the browser window.
Press key [ 1 ] or [ 2 ] or [ 3 ] to redraw with "low" or "medium" or "high" quality resolution (default is “low” quality).
Press [ S ] at any moment to save a screenshot.
Press [ L ] to disable/enable "LIVE" mode (enabled by default).
Press [ P ] to pause/unpause live drawing when in "LIVE" mode.
Press [ Q ] to redraw and save using the best quality (9900x7000 resolution, the file should be around 30 Mo).

Viewing in desktop Chrome is recommended for the best results. Made with p5js only.
